         <abstract>
            <p>If the quadrature rule Q is applied to the function f, then the error can in many situations be bounded by ρ&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt;(Q)|f&lt;sup&gt;(s)&lt;/sup&gt;|&lt;sub&gt;∞&lt;/sub&gt;, where ρ&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt;(Q) is independent of f. We obtain the asymptotics of these numbers for the Gaussian method Q&lt;sup&gt;G&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; (n = 1, 2, ...) with very general weight functions and show that ρ&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt;(Q&lt;sup&gt;G&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;) is (asymptotically) an upper bound for ρ&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt;(Q), if Q is any quadrature rule with the same degree as Q&lt;sup&gt;G&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;.</p>
          </abstract>
